t issue of Arion would come out in a month’s time. A postscript contained a courteous request:

Allow us to put, ‘a novel by Ilya Annenski,’ and not, as you suggest, ‘I. Annenski,’ otherwise there might be some confusion with the ‘last swan of Tsarskoe Selo,’ as Gumilyov calls him.



Ilya Borisovich answered:

Yes, of course, I just did not know that there already existed an author writing under that name. I am delighted my work will be printed. Please have the kindness to send me